metricapp.utility.stateTransitionUtils.metricTransition

Class MetricStateTransitionCommand

  • java.lang.Object
    • metricapp.utility.stateTransitionUtils.metricTransition.MetricStateTransitionCommand
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    StateTransitionCommand
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    ApprovedToOnUpdate, ApprovedToSuspendend, CreatedToOnUpdate, OnUpdateToPending, PendingToApproved, PendingToRejected, RejectedToOnUpdate, RejectedToSuspended

    public abstract class MetricStateTransitionCommand
extends java.lang.Object
implements StateTransitionCommand
    This abstract class is the prototype of a Command, configured to be used for Metric transitions. It has 2 attributes, that MUST be not null during execution.

    Child classes MUST implement a 2 parameters constructor that calls the method in this class:

    e.g. public CreatedToOnUpdate(Element before, Element after){

    super(before, after);

    }

    Child should overrides execute method and call it like super class method:

    e.g. public void execute(){

    super.execute();

    foo(things);

    ...

    }
